climbs.name: The Wambulance
climbs.fa: Adam Van Straten and Kraig Decker

content.description: Follows the arete.  SDS A few big moves to start until a ledge is reached half way up.  from there its cake
content.protection: a few pads and a spotter.  there is a pit right where you whould fall.
content.location: follow the right of The Sound of the Life of the Mind

climbs.name: Sticky Foot
climbs.fa: Adam Van Straten and Kraig Decker

content.description: follow the left crack.  pretty mellow till the top where the crack flares a bit and you must smear with you feet.

climbs.name: The Sound Of The Life Of The Mind (direct)

content.description: SDS Head straight up the bulge.  Good start holds turn to poor crimps quickly.  Very technical. Took months for me to figure out the Beta.

climbs.name: Skeeter Snack
climbs.fa: Adam Van Straten and Kraig Decker

content.description: the right of the two cracks on the boulder.  Lie back the rail till it ends.  use a poor slopper and high feet to get to the horizontal crack then top out.  Easier for taller folks.

climbs.name: (project) The Sound Of The Life Of The Mind

content.description: start on the right arete on traverse the horizontal crack into the direct version of this problem.

Small area near North Little Fox.  Currently contains 3 easy problems, on harder, and a tough project.  THe easier ones are no gimme though, the crux on each on is up high.  Nice little area that could have a few more problems added.
